Chilean Stocks: Empresas La Polar, Paz, Quinenco Decline

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-06-24T21:25:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/chilean-stocks-empresas-la-polar-paz-quinenco-decline.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index was little changed at 4,696.35. The  MSCI
Chile (MXCL)  index gained 0.3 percent to 2,765.52.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)  , the Chilean retailer
that increased loan-loss provisions after detecting consumer-
credit irregularities, dropped 0.7 percent to 630.68 pesos.
Shares had gained 36 percent in the previous two trading
sessions after falling 67 percent in the prior two days.  Shareholders on June 22 approved a proposal to sell new
stock as the department-store operator seeks to avert a second
bankruptcy in 12 years.  Volume was almost twice its daily three-month average.  Paz Corp SA (PAZ)  , a Santiago-based homebuilder,
declined 1.4 percent to 410.58 pesos. Santiago-based Paz is
seeking regulatory approval to sell as much as $69.3 million of
bonds, according to a statement posted on the website of  Chile ’s
securities regulator.  Quinenco SA (QUINENC)   fell 0.3 percent to 1,610.1 pesos
as the holding company of Chile’s Luksic family sold 7 million
“unidades de fomento,” Chile’s inflation-adjusted accounting
unit, or $324 million of seven- and 21-year bonds. The 21-year
notes were priced to yield 3.95 percent while the seven-year
bonds were sold at 3.49 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York 
